    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1903-10-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1903-10-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="103"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d103">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Beaupré</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-10-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 9, 1903</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your No.
                    131, of the 8th ultimo, reporting the hostile demonstration on the part of
                    Colombians against the Syrian “Turks.”</p>
                <p>The Department approves your course in requesting the protection of the Colombian
                    Government for such of them as are naturalized citizens of the United
                    States.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
